review_blob: As a blue moon fan I expected much more from them, but this beer is dead to me.  I felt like I was drinking cardboard, it looked like a full beer but was severely lacking flavor.
beer_name: Blue Moon Full Moon Winter Ale

review_blob: This beer is pretty much good times in a bottle and has been responsible for many of my sunday hangovers.  As a pale lager you might not find anything more quenching.  Once it hits your lips it feels soooo good.
Rich hoppy taste, with a hint of pine and some bitterness.  Has a rich texture with and pours a nice head, no IPAs will ever be the same!
Overall a great beer.  Tastes light and refreshing with a sweet strawberry taste.  One of my favorite fruit beers.
A beer with several different flavors, nutmetg, cherries and vanilla, that make this full bodied brew delicious.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: It has a unique flavor, with an appetizing aroma.  However, its taste is seemingly like starburst mixed with a light beer, which prevented me from finishing my case.
A delicious brew, I would have never guessed that it was 6.7 %.  It delivered on the hops, and had only a mild bitterness.
